ducing students from Hispanic and Black neighborhoods in the west and south sides of Chicago to the Russian culture and language, with an emphasis on poet, playwright, and novelist Alexander Pushkin. Through the lens of modern evolutionary thought, students adopt not only a new and different language and culture, but also a different sort of literary hero, one whose African heritage within the majority culture speaks to them directly. This inspiring and compelling story provides fascinating insights into Russia's national poet, brings the sciences and humanities together, and provides new directions in teaching young people from historically disadvantaged backgrounds.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCollege preparation programszWisconsinzMadisonvCase studies. 0aEducationxPhilosophy. 0aRussian languagexStudy and teaching (Secondary)zUnited States. 0aRussian literaturey19th centuryxStudy and teaching (Secondary)zUnited States. 0aSocial evolution. 0aSummer schoolszWisconsinzMadisonvCase studies. 0aTeachingxMethodology. 7aEDUCATION / Teaching Methods & Materials / Arts & Humanities.2bisacsh  aPushkin, Diversity, Darwin, Cultural Evolution, Teaching Underserved Communities, Innovation in Humanistic Research, Inner-city schools.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAcademic Studies Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311102354008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2023 Part 2z978311117804208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Comm 2023 Englishz978311131910008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyt